description:
This is a 15 minute workout called 'Yoga for Vertigo  |  15-Minute Yoga' from the channel Yoga With Adriene.
The workout falls under Flexibility/Yoga.
It's suitable for Beginner and Intermediate fitness levels.
The workout has a The Zen Flow and The Reboot Workout vibe.
The technique difficulty is Beginner and Intermediate.
The effort required is Light.

Original workout description: Join me for this 15-minute Yoga For Vertigo session. Begin this relaxing practice by improving blood circulation and balancing the hemispheres of the brain with breath work, or pranayama.

This gentle session is designed to activate and calm the parasympathetic nervous system.
This short practice could be beneficial for those who are recovering from injury, TBI (traumatic brain injury), or those who are working with Glaucoma.

Be mindful, take it slow, and Find What Feels Good.

Namaste.

For more videos like this, try this Yoga For Glaucoma and Vertigo Playllist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLui6Eyny-UzyfTUQJWjiCn3Gdi8snJ5fW
